Package optional.lab2

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Auxiliary
    Auxiliary is an additional class to store the supplies and demands line per line It consists of : A supply for a source A demand for a destination A value that stores the cost from a source to destination
    Destination
    Destination is a class to describe the destinations in the given problem Each destination has : The amount of commodities it can receives from the sources A name
    Factory
    Factory is the class to describe the type of a source
    Lab2Optional  
    Problem
    Problem is the class to describe the given transportation problem It consists of : An array of sources Source An array of destinations Destination An array of supplies (for each of the sources) An array of demands (for each of the destinations) A cost matrix, in which we store the costs from a source to a destination A linked list LinkedList to store the solution
    Source
    Source is an abstract class to describe the sources in the given problem Each source has : The amount of commodities it can provide to the destinations A name
    Warehouse
    Warehouse is the class to describe the type of a source
